{
  "doc_id": "48727",
  "text": "The lignin content was determined as Klason lignin and acid-soluble lignin with the following pretreatment: the extractives-free bark residues (2 g) were first extracted with 3% KOH (w/v) in EtOH for 2 h at 70 • C to remove suberin and polymeric phenolic acids and then filtered. The residues were dried at 105 • C overnight. The total lignin content was determined on dry residues (0.5 g) as described by [CITATION_1] .",
